        <title>About</title>
        <link>https://carlokaram.github.io/page/about/</link>
        <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://carlokaram.github.io/page/about/</guid>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m &lt;strong&gt;Carlo Karam&lt;/strong&gt;, a doctoral candidate at &lt;strong&gt;Grenoble INP&lt;/strong&gt;, working in the &lt;strong&gt;MODUS team&lt;/strong&gt; (Modeling and Optimal Decisions for Uncertain Systems) at &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://www.gipsa-lab.grenoble-inp.fr/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;GIPSA-lab&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, co-advised by &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=npX9VIgAAAAJ&amp;amp;hl=fr&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mirko Fiacchini&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://matteotacchi.wordpress.com/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Matteo Tacchi-Bénard&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. My research focuses on characterizing &lt;strong&gt;probabilistic reachable and invariant sets&lt;/strong&gt; for stochastic model predictive control (SMPC). My work leverages &lt;strong&gt;convex and polynomial optimization&lt;/strong&gt; to estimate these sets accurately and efficiently, enabling practical SMPC implementations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before my PhD, I completed a &lt;strong&gt;Bachelor&amp;rsquo;s Degree in Mechanical Engineering&lt;/strong&gt; at the &lt;strong&gt;American University of Beirut (2016–2020)&lt;/strong&gt;, followed by a &lt;strong&gt;Master’s in Mechatronic Engineering&lt;/strong&gt; at &lt;strong&gt;Politecnico di Torino (2020–2022)&lt;/strong&gt;. I then worked as a &lt;strong&gt;Junior Control Systems Engineer at Dumarey Softronix (2022–2024)&lt;/strong&gt;, where I focused on MPC for selective catalytic reduction (SCR) in diesel engines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can check out my &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://carlokaram.github.io/files/cv.pdf&#34; &gt;CV&lt;/a&gt; for more details.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
